        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1946-08-15T04:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1946-08-15T04:00:00-05:00" n="17" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d17">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">893.00/8–1546: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Chargé in the Soviet Union</hi> (<persName type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Durbrow</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Moscow</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1946-08-15T12:00:00+03:00">August 15, 1946—noon</date>.<lb/>[Received August 15—7:58
                        a.m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>3202. Printed document has been received by British Embassy here from London
                    containing report of British Ambassador at Nanking regarding conversation with
                    Chou En-lai, Communist representative <pb facs="0056" n="46" xml:id="pg_46"/> at
                    Nanking. Chou reportedly complained to Ambassador of American interference in
                    China and support of KMT.</p>
                <p>He was said to have suggested that Ambassador recommend to Bevin<note n="48" xml:id="d17fn48">Ernest Bevin, British Secretary of State for Foreign
                        Affairs.</note> that Bevin and Molotov<note n="49" xml:id="d17fn49">V. M.
                        Molotov, Soviet Minister for Foreign Affairs.</note> call Byrnes to account
                    for violation of Moscow Foreign Ministers Agreement on China.<note n="50" xml:id="d17fn50">Department of State <hi rend="italic">Bulletin</hi>,
                        December 30, 1945, p. 1030.</note>
                </p>
                <p>Repeated to London 344; Paris, 303.<note n="51" xml:id="d17fn51">Repeated to the
                        Embassy in China in Department’s telegram No. 611, August 15, 4 p.m.</note>
                </p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Durbrow</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
